<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,267,1421]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,409,267,293]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">External characters.</emphasis>
Wing span 
<quantity box="[552,631,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="12.0">12mm</quantity>
. Frons, vertex, collar, thorax, tegulae, patagia and legs white; labial palpi white, dorsal yellow-brown; antenna yellow brown. Abdomen pale brown dorsally, ventral body white. Forewing silvery white; medial line pale fuscous, from middle of costa to discocellulares, then bent to inner margin; submarginal line pale fuscous, from costa to vein M 
<number box="[870,878,400,414]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
then bent inwards to anal angle; marginal area suffused with orange-yellow longitudinal fasciae along the veins, with 
<number box="[999,1014,425,451]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
black spots between M 
<number box="[1296,1304,441,455]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
and Cu 
<number box="[1398,1406,441,455]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
; a fuscous marginal line from apex to middle of outer margin; cilia silvery white, suffused with fuscous. Hindwing silvery white; cilia silvery white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,267,1421]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,394,544,570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Uncus strong, the apex pointed, ventral with a tuft of thick setae; gnathos tapering pointed, slightly curved to dorsal; tegumen triangular; valva broad, protruding at apex, costal arm strong, much longer than valva and apart from valva, the middle of costal arm with a spine-like process, the apex of costal arm strong pointed; juxta plate-shaped, apical with two papillate processes; aedeagus elongate, without cornutus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,267,1421]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,421,737,763]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Anal papillae weakly fused, with dense setae; apophysis posterioris about 
<number box="[1351,1362,738,764]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1373,1390,738,764]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
the length of apophysis anterioris; ostium bursae funnel-shaped, slightly sclerotized; ductus bursae long, swollen at middle, corpus bursae rounded, with two rhombus-like signa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
