<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,267,1421]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1162,1188]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is different with other species by forewing with 
<number box="[1062,1077,1163,1189]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
black spots on marginal area, while other species of this genus with only 
<number box="[687,702,1202,1228]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
spot except 
<taxonomicName box="[858,1036,1202,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocasis">
<emphasis box="[858,1036,1202,1227]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">G. xanthocasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[1055,1070,1202,1228]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
spots). In male genitalia, this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[394,529,1241,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidusa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[394,529,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">G. albidusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[537,631,1240,1266]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[537,631,1240,1266]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but the costal arm longer than valva and middle of it with a spinelike process, while 
<taxonomicName box="[383,519,1279,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidusa">
<emphasis box="[383,519,1279,1304]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">G. albidusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the costal arm shorter than valva and middle of it without the spine-like process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,267,1421]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1356,1382]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[783,806,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">di</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis box="[890,968,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="53">stigma</emphasis>
”, corresponding to the 
<number box="[1245,1260,1356,1382]" pageId="13" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
black spots on marginal area of forewing.
</paragraph>
